=== Mibbit Webchat ===
Donate link: http://example.com/
Tags: irc, chat, mibbit
Requires at least: 2.7
Tested up to: 2.9
Stable tag: trunk

This plugin makes it possible to add a Mibbit widget to your blog and/or page.

== Description ==

Mibbit is an online chat client. 
Mibbit supports a variety of Platforms including the main PC browsers, the wii, Nokia N800, iPhone, and probably a lot more.
It does this without any plugins. Just javascript. Mibbit currently supports IRC and Twitter, with other protocols due to be supported soon. 
You can also use the Mibbit widget to provide real time chat on your own website. 

== Installation ==

1. Upload `mibbit-webchat` to the `/wp-content/plugins/` directory
2. Activate the plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in WordPress
3. Place <!-- mibbit_webchat --> in your page and/or blog

== Frequently Asked Questions ==

= What can I do with this plugin? =
You can give your users a place to chat.

